C.6 = unattended-approval notification path. Shipped with reply-to-SMS as
the operator-facing UX (instead of the spec's link-to-UI flow, since
app.trybasics.ai has no /approvals UI today and replying is more natural
on phone anyway).

Files added / changed:
  - worker/src/approvals/notifier.ts       SES + Sendblue direct send; SMS body
                                            is "Approval needed: <tool> (<reason>).
                                            Reply YES to approve, NO to deny."
  - worker/src/approvals/notifier.test.ts  16 unit tests (was 14, +2 for new body)
  - worker/src/approvals/await.ts          fire-and-forget call to notifyApproval
                                            after publishing approval_requested
  - api/src/routes/sendblue-inbound.ts     POST /webhooks/sendblue: from_number→
                                            workspace lookup, parseReply (YES/NO),
                                            UPDATE + INSERT cloud_activity + pg_notify,
                                            confirmation SMS back to operator.
  - api/src/routes/sendblue-inbound.test.ts 11 unit tests
  - api/src/app.ts                         mount sendblueInboundRoute under /webhooks

Auth model for inbound: phone-pair, no JWT or signature.
  - from_number must match a workspace's `agent_settings.approval_phone`
  - to_number must match SENDBLUE_FROM_NUMBER (defense in depth)
  - Unknown sender → 200 silently (don't echo "unauthorized" over SMS)

